# Full Paths in Terminal Instructions

When instructing the user to run a command in their terminal, **always provide the full absolute path** — never use relative paths.

- Bad: "Navigate to `fivefold-ios/` and run `npx expo start`"
- Good: "In your terminal, run: `cd /Users/jz/Desktop/guthub/project-1/fivefold-ios && npx expo start`"

This applies to all terminal instructions: cd, npx, node, npm, firebase, git, etc.
